  "date": "2026-03-19",
  "publisher": "SPiER Project (FHIR translation)",
  "description": "FHIR Questionnaire representation of the C-SSRS Screen Version (Recent). A 6-item suicide risk assessment with three-tier risk stratification (Low/Moderate/High). Questions 1-2 are always asked; Questions 3-5 are conditional on Q2=Yes; Question 6 (suicidal behavior) is always asked. This is the brief screener version \u2014 see also the Full Lifetime/Recent version for comprehensive assessment.",
  "purpose": "Suicide risk assessment and stratification. Risk tiers: Q1-Q2 positive = Low Risk, Q3-Q4 positive = Moderate Risk, Q5 or Q6 positive = High Risk. Used after positive screening (e.g., PHQ-9 Item 9, ASQ) to determine risk level and guide clinical response.",
  "copyright": "\u00a9 2008 The Research Foundation for Mental Hygiene, Inc. Developed by Posner, K.; Brent, D.; Lucas, C.; Gould, M.; Stanley, B.; Brown, G.; Fisher, P.; Zelazny, J.; Burke, A.; Oquendo, M.; Mann, J. For inquiries and training: posnerk@nyspi.columbia.edu",
